      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STARLIGHT TWIX (4) missed the frame last time in a Grade 5/6, colliding with another runner to finish a 1.75 lengths fourth over 300m at Mandurah. Returns to a course where she has performed well. Rates on top in this line up. BARIUM (2) is an honest type who is lining up for her first start here. Comes here a winner after using the inside draw to advantage last time, scoring by a nose at Mandurah over 300m (17.47). The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. One of the leading chances again. RAPIDO MYSTIQUE (1) goes very well this trip starting 21 times for seven wins and four minors. Below best last time at Mandurah (17.58) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 7 length sixth. With even luck and a clean start should be thereabouts. SHINBONER PIXIE (5) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish.",
